name: Fahima Mokhtari Allal
headline: Computer Science Engineer | Python, Node.js, React, PostgreSQL
creator: False
bio:
I am a versatile Computer Science Engineer with 3 years experience, in full-stack development, cloud infrastructure, and software architecture. My passion lies in solving complex problems and creating user-focused solutions. Proficient in Python, JavaScript, Node.js, Java, and C, I have built scalable and reliable applications across various platforms.

In my professional roles, I have deployed applications to cloud platforms, enhancing both scalability and reliability. I have also led the development of automated CI/CD pipelines, improving the efficiency of deployment processes.

Beyond development, I have experience teaching software engineering principles and software systems design at university, and I helped improving students' practical skills by 25% and achieving a 9/10 satisfaction rating. I enjoy guiding aspiring developers, helping them master the fundamentals through hands-on courses that enhance their practical skills.

Collaboration is central to my approach. I thrive in team environments, where I contribute to projects that improve user experience and operational efficiency. I am dedicated to continuous learning, always seeking to stay ahead in the fast-evolving tech landscape.

Skills:
Programming Languages: JavaScript, TypeScript, React, Next.js, Python, Java, C, C++, Go, PHP, Bash, HTML, CSS, SQL.
Technologies & Frameworks: Node.js, AWS, GCP, Docker, Kubernetes, WordPress.
Tools: Git, Sparx Enterprise Architect.
Databases: PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQL Server, Redis, MongoDB, DynamoDB.

Contact:
I am open to new opportunities. If you are interested in my profile, feel free to reach out to me at:
Email: df_mokhtari@esi.dz

headline: Machine Learning Engineer | MSc. Data Science & AI
creator: False
bio:
As a dedicated Data Scientist at Intelligent Valley, my role revolves around deploying machine learning algorithms and advanced data analytics to tackle complex business issues across various sectors. With a freshly minted MSc in Data Science and Artificial Intelligence from Innopolis University, I bring the latest academic insights straight to the table, enhancing our data-driven strategies.

My technical toolkit, refined through rigorous academic research and hands-on client projects, includes Python, SQL, and an array of machine learning libraries. The collaborative efforts of our diverse team have been pivotal in delivering actionable insights and predictive solutions, all aimed at bolstering business intelligence and driving innovation forward.

creator: False

bio:
Feel free to text me anytime.
✌🏽😁🤙🏽

The mainline of all my previous (and current) job places is GIS. I love to find, analyze, generate ideas, make improvements and create something new and my job allows me to do it.

To connect with people is my pleasure. It is amazing how more work and how much faster we can make a deal done when we collaborate with co-workers. I’m really a troubleshooter. I love hard cases. My passion is to get hard deals done. Always learning is my favorite goal. There is always space for improvements (and maneuver). And the most brilliant benefit of learning is to implement new knowledge into the work and make things easier.

I am a part of a professional Geomatics group at Innopolis University. We work together creating and maintaining new services for our customers. Acquisition, analyzing, programming, processing, retention, and visualization of data are the parts of our daily job. We always improve our workflows and take on new challenges.

In my spare time, I like to study English because it really helps me to connect with people. And also I love to play and write music.

name: Gaspard Baye
headline: Cyber AI Ph.D. Candidate | Ex. Security AI Red Team@ Qualcomm | Speaker @ DEFCON, Bsides, OWASP, TDI | OSCP | PNPT | CEH | Nokia, Ford Motors Hall of Fame | 1x CVE | MSc | ex-NSBE chapter President | Leader
creator: True
bio: Gaspard Baye is a PhD candidate and a security AI scientist with over 5+ years of experience developing AI-driven offensive and defensive security applications. He has been recognized with 10+ novel AI research publications in prestigious conferences such as NeurIPS, HASP, and IEEE Access, accumulating 80+ citations. He is a recognized CVE holder with certifications, including AI security and Governance, OSCP, PNPT, Scrum, NSE1, NSE2, and CEH Practical. His work has been showcased at cybersecurity conferences such as DEFCON, OWASP, BSides, and The Diana Initiative. Through a dedicated vulnerability disclosure program, he's identified and helped remediate over 20+ critical security vulnerabilities, earning Hall of Fame recognitions from Nokia and Ford Motors.

bio:
I am passionate about software development. I worked mainly with Android Native Development. But I also have some experience with Unity, C#, C, and Go. name: Hamza Salem
headline: CTO & Technical Consultant & Developer Relations & Blockchain Developer &(PhD) 🇯🇴 🇷🇺
creator: True
bio:
I am Hamza Salem, a highly skilled professional with extensive experience and expertise in the field of computer science and software engineering. I hold a PhD in Computer Science, a Master's degree in Software Engineering, and I am a Microsoft Certified Professional. With a strong background as a Computer Engineer, Web and Mobile Developer, and Blockchain Engineer (specializing in Ethereum and Solidity), I have successfully undertaken various roles throughout my career.

In my previous positions, I have excelled as a Front-End Developer, proficient in Angular and Vue.js, as well as Mobile Development using Ionic and ReactNative. Additionally, I have worked with Python frameworks such as Odoo and Django. As a Full Stack Developer, I have experience working with Node.js and Angular.

In my current role, I lead an engineering team responsible for developing STYLE Protocol, which is one of our core products. This team consists of 2-3 senior React/blockchain engineers. As the team lead, I am accountable for the technical delivery of the squad and ensure efficient and effective implementation with a high standard of performance.

I provide guidance and support to my team members through regular 1:1 meetings, empowering them to deliver on our technical vision and fostering their career development. As the counterpart of the product owner, I align the technical strategy with the product roadmap and priorities. I act as the subject-matter expert for engineering within the squad, assisting in architectural decisions.

One of my key responsibilities is ensuring a smooth development process and constantly improving it. I actively contribute to creating a collaborative, inclusive, and vibrant remote engineering culture that aligns with our guiding principles. Additionally, I handle the recruitment and staffing of technical resources, ensuring that the squad has the necessary skills and capabilities within the allocated budget.

Throughout my career, I have also been actively involved in open-source projects, dedicating my weekends to writing code and contributing to the community.
Some fun project that am doing in weekends:

name: Emmanuel Lwele
headline: 🦾🥷🏾 Ph.D. Candidate in Robotics | Machine Learning | 👨🏾‍💻 Software Engineer | 📱 iOS & Mobile App Developer | 📊 AI, Digital Twins & Surrogate Modeling Expert | 👨🏾‍🏫 Educator
creator: True
bio:
PhD Researcher exploring the intersections of Robotics, Machine Learning, physics-informed neural networks and Digital Twin technology with a focus on industrial applications. Currently delving into AI-based surrogate modelling for digital twins within industrial processes under the Advanced Food Innovation Centre, led by Dr Hongweei Zhang and supervised by Professor  Alex Shenfield.

Passionate about the application of learning algorithms in enhancing the autonomy of robots, cars, and drones. My research endeavours aim to advance the understanding and implementation of AI-driven surrogate models for digital twins, revolutionizing industrial processes.

🎓 Education:

    PhD in Robotics & Machine Learning | Sheffield Hallam University
    Master's in Financial Engineering | WQU
    Master's in Computer Science & Computer Engineering | Specialization in Models, Methods, and Software for Project Solution Analysis

🔧 Skills:

    Proficient in Programming: C/C++, Python, Java, MATLAB, Julia 
    Strong grasp of Control Theory
    Extensive experience in project solution analysis, modelling, and software development

Keen on collaborative opportunities and exploring innovative solutions at the intersection of technology and industry. Let's connect and propel advancements in Robotics and AI together!

name: Kevin Khanda
headline: CTO & CPO and Founding Team Member – Uzum, Co-founder – KazanExpress, Forbes 30 under 30
creator: False
bio:
As co-founder of the marketplace with next day delivery KazanExpress, I played a pivotal role in bootstrapping the platform's product and technological foundation. The company was sold as a strategic acquisition to Magnit and later evolved into Magnit Market - an e-commerce inside a traditional retailer. Our team's innovation yielded a yearly GMV run rate exceeding $480 million, and we achieved the recognition of being the fastest delivery service within all marketplaces of the region market.

At Uzum, I continued to leverage this expertise, leading product and software development initiatives that challenge and transform the traditional market model in Uzbekistan. I was in charge of the team that bootstrapped and developed the first marketplace in Uzbekistan - Uzum Market, the very first and most recognizable product from the Uzum ecosystem.

Now, as Chief Product & Technology Officer at Uzum, my focus is on directing the evolution of our digital ecosystem, which aims to transition street bazaars to online commerce with seamless access to digital finances. My leadership in this domain is not only reshaping consumer behavior but also empowering local businesses to thrive in a digital-first economy. We are steadfast in our commitment to delivering excellence and innovation in the e-commerce and fintech landscapes.

school_2: Orta Doğu Teknik Üniversitesi / Middle East Technical University
bio:
As a software development engineer in test (SDET) and quality assurance (QA) engineer, I have over four years of experience in developing and automating test cases and scenarios for various systems and applications, using Java, Scala, Python, and other tools. I previously worked in FinTech and Telecom sectors, where I have developed and supported testing frameworks, collected and reported performance metrics, and collaborated with development and manual QA teams. 

I have a bachelor's degree in computer science from Innopolis University, where I also worked as a research assistant in the Cyber-Physical Systems Lab, focusing on agile adoption in industrial companies. I have won multiple awards and scholarships for my academic and research achievements, such as the third prize at the ESEC/FSE 2019 Student Research Competition, the ACM-W scholarship, and the Erasmus+ grant. I am passionate about agile mindset and leadership, and I believe they go beyond the professional life.

name: Ramil Askarov
headline: Blockchain Engineer (Go | Cosmos-SDK | Solidity)
creator: False
bio:
With over six years in software development and a three-year focus on blockchain, I've honed skills in Cosmos SDK and smart contract development, specializing in Golang/Solidity. My expertise extends to scalable web services, utilizing HTTP/REST/RPC/WS, databases (PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Redis), message brokers (RabbitMQ, Kafka), cloud platforms (GCloud, AWS), and Docker.
Highlights of my career include leading a legacy system's architectural revamp for better scalability and blockchain integration, developing automation and dockerization in blockchain setups, and pioneering Cosmovisor for system upgrades. I'm also exploring AI to boost productivity, committed to continuous learning and leading-edge solutions.

name: Shinnazar Seytnazarov
headline: Assistant Professor at Nazarbayev University | Computer communications and networks, Distributed systems
creator: False
bio:
I'm interested in solving different research problems in all layers of TCP/IP protocol stack, although my major focus is performance improvement/evaluation/modeling of wireless networks. 
Here are some problems that I currently work on with my colleagues and students:
– Performance improvement/evaluation/modeling of wireless networks.
– Wireless sensing using ML/AI.
– Practical radio resource management (RRM) in a dense Wi-Fi environment.
– Analysis and optimization of TCP’s congestion control for lossy wireless links.
– Adaptation of the FEC ratio for real-time web-based communications.
– Consensus in SDN using blockchains.
– Distributed multi-objective routing.

Feel free to contact me if you want to cooperate in solving similar research problems.

name: Dmitrii Desiatkin
headline: Senior developer at Huawei Hong Kong RnD center
creator: False
bio:
For the last two years I studied internals of web layout engines: Blink, Servo, flutter - web apps.

Previously my efforts are concentrated on studying different SLAM, sensor fusion, and sensor calibration techniques. To be more specific I have studied and tested several Pose and Landmark graph SLAM techniques, have done camera intrinsic and extrinsic sensors calibrations (i.e. lidar to camera calibration and camera to camera calibrations). In the sphere of mapping, I have participated in the process of the creation of large-scale lidar maps (we have mapped a highway road).

Also, I have experience in Lidar and Visual odometry. Worked with different versions of Normal Distribution Transform (NDT), Generalized Iterative Closest Point (GICP), and Lego-LOAM styled algorithms. 
In the field of visual odometry I have tested mainly feature-based algorithms, I know that in recent years with the widespread of GPU more companies chose Direct visual methods, however, despite I know the theory I have not worked with them. However, I have worked with several AI-based landmark algorithms e.g. Superpoint; and trained several Neural Networks during my master program.

I am often working with using docker containers and developing the product using containerization. Sometimes I also do containerization using direct Linux system calls (cgroup).

Concerning sensor fusion, I have done it mostly in a classic way by using the Kalman Filtering approach.

Note about university: 
Established in 2012, Innopolis University is an English-speaking university in Russia, primarily focused on teaching and research in the fields of IT and Robotics. 
In 2021, the university ranked 683rd in the world according to https://roundranking.com

My hobbies:
Hardware - I love to research different computer gear. Recently I have bought an old server for my home lab. In near future, I want to assemble my quadrocopter. Also, I have played a lot with Raspberry-like SOCs. During my undergraduate studies, I had little experience in programming microcontrollers (Intel 8051 SiLabs chip).
Music - I like good old and modern Metal.
Handicraft - Can watch videos of skillful craftsmen for hours.

Обмениваюсь опытом и идеями с другими разработчиками
